{
    "info": {
        "_postman_id": "fixmate-api-collection",
        "name": "FixMate API",
        "description": "# FixMate API\n\nHome services marketplace backend — Customers book Technicians for jobs, pay via Stripe/SSLCommerz, and leave Reviews. Admins moderate users, bookings, and Categories.\n\nAll variables this collection needs (`baseUrl`, `accessToken`, `bookingId`, etc.) are **collection-scoped** — they live only inside this collection and will not collide with any other project's Postman globals or environments. You do not need to import a separate environment file; just import this collection and start running requests. Open **Collection → Variables** tab if you want to inspect/reset them by hand.\n\n---\n\n## Seeded accounts (run `npm run seed` once against the target database)\n\n| Role | Email | Password |\n|---|---|---|\n| Admin | `admin@fixmate.dev` (or your `ADMIN_EMAIL`) | your `ADMIN_PASSWORD` |\n| Technician (sample) | `sam.technician@fixmate.dev` | `Secret123!` |\n\nThe seed also creates a `Plumbing` category and a `Kitchen sink repair` service under the sample technician, so `Bookings > Create` has something real to book immediately — no manual data entry needed.\n\n---\n\n## The three role journeys (who can do what, end to end)\n\n### Customer journey\n1. `User > Register or Login` — register with no `role` field (defaults to CUSTOMER), or comment in the CUSTOMER login block.\n2. `Categories > Get All`, `Services > Get All` / `Get One`, `Technicians > Get All` / `Get One` — browse, no auth needed.\n3. `Bookings > Create` — book a technician for a service + time slot. Saves `bookingId`.\n4. `Payments > Create` — only works once the booking is `ACCEPTED` (a Technician must accept it first — see below). Opens a real Stripe test checkout.\n5. Complete payment via Stripe CLI (`npm run stripe:webhook`) or ask the backend owner to confirm it — booking moves to `PAID`.\n6. `Bookings > Get All` / `Get One` — track status the whole way through.\n7. `Bookings > Cancel` — allowed any time before the booking reaches `IN_PROGRESS`.\n8. Once a Technician marks the job `COMPLETED`, `Reviews > Create` — one review per booking, rating 1-5.\n\n### Technician journey\n1. `User > Register or Login` — register with `role: \"TECHNICIAN\"` (comment in that variant), or use the seeded `sam.technician@fixmate.dev` account. Registering also auto-creates an empty Technician Profile.\n2. `Technician Self-Service > Update My Profile` — set skills, years of experience, availability flag.\n3. `Technician Self-Service > Update My Availability` — replace the full weekly schedule in one call.\n4. *(Service creation has no API yet — the seed script creates one sample service for you; ask the backend owner to add more directly if needed.)*\n5. `Technician Self-Service > Get My Bookings` — see incoming requests.\n6. `Technician Self-Service > Update Booking Status` — one endpoint drives the whole state machine:\n   `REQUESTED → ACCEPTED or DECLINED`, then `PAID → IN_PROGRESS`, then `IN_PROGRESS → COMPLETED`. Any other transition is rejected with a 400 explaining exactly which transitions are legal from the current state.\n\n### Admin journey\n1. `Auth > Login` with the seeded Admin credentials above (there is **no self-registration path for Admin** — by design, nobody can grant themselves admin through a public endpoint).\n2. `Admin > Get All Users` — see every user, any role.\n3. `Admin > Ban User` / `Unban User` — toggles `activeStatus`. Verified to take effect **immediately**: a banned user's existing token stops working on their very next request, and they cannot log in again while blocked.\n4. `Admin > Get All Bookings` — oversee every booking in the system regardless of owner.\n5. `Admin > Get All Categories` / `Create Category` — manage the category list customers and technicians browse/filter by. Fails with 409 on a duplicate name.\n\n---\n\n## How auth works in this collection\nEvery `Login` and `Register (role: TECHNICIAN)` request has a **Test script** that automatically saves `accessToken`, `refreshToken`, and the relevant id (`customerId`/`technicianId`) into this collection's variables. Every protected request below sends `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}` — you never copy-paste a token by hand. Just run Login for whichever role you want to act as; it overwrites `accessToken` for the next requests you run.\n\n`Bookings > Create`, `Payments > Create`, `Admin > Create Category` similarly auto-save `bookingId` / `paymentId` / `categoryId` for you.\n\n---\n\n## Error responses\nEvery error (validation failure, not-found, unauthorized, server error) returns the same JSON shape:\n```json\n{ \"success\": false, \"message\": \"...\", \"errorDetails\": null }\n```\nValidation failures populate `errorDetails` with a list of `{ field, message }` — see any request marked with invalid example data for a live sample.",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "variable": [
        { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:5000", "type": "default" },
        { "key": "accessToken", "value": "", "type": "secret" },
        { "key": "refreshToken", "value": "", "type": "secret" },
        { "key": "customerId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
        { "key": "technicianId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
        { "key": "adminId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
        { "key": "categoryId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
        { "key": "serviceId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
        { "key": "bookingId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
        { "key": "paymentId", "value": "", "type": "default" }
    ],
    "item": [
        {
            "name": "Auth",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Login",
                    "event": [
                        {
                            "listen": "test",
                            "script": {
                                "type": "text/javascript",
                                "exec": [
                                    "const res = pm.response.json();",
                                    "if (res && res.data && res.data.accessToken) {",
                                    "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.data.accessToken);",
                                    "    pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', res.data.refreshToken);",
                                    "    const role = res.data.user.role;",
                                    "    if (role === 'CUSTOMER') pm.collectionVariables.set('customerId', res.data.user.id);",
                                    "    if (role === 'TECHNICIAN') pm.collectionVariables.set('technicianId', res.data.user.id);",
                                    "    if (role === 'ADMIN') pm.collectionVariables.set('adminId', res.data.user.id);",
                                    "    console.log('Saved accessToken/refreshToken for role: ' + role);",
                                    "}",
                                    "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                                    "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                                    "});"
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"jane.customer@fixmate.dev\",\n  \"password\": \"Secret123!\"\n}\n\n// -- TECHNICIAN login (comment out the block above, uncomment this one) --\n// {\n//   \"email\": \"sam.technician@fixmate.dev\",\n//   \"password\": \"Secret123!\"\n// }\n\n// -- ADMIN login (must already be seeded directly in the DB -- no self-register) --\n// {\n//   \"email\": \"admin@fixmate.dev\",\n//   \"password\": \"Secret123!\"\n// }"
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "login"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** anyone (public).\n\nActive body: CUSTOMER. To log in as a different role, delete the active JSON block and uncomment the TECHNICIAN or ADMIN block below it (they're valid JSON once uncommented — the `//` lines above/below them are the only thing making them inactive).\n\nSaves `accessToken` + `refreshToken` + the matching id into collection variables automatically, based on the `role` in the response."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Refresh Token",
                    "event": [
                        {
                            "listen": "test",
                            "script": {
                                "type": "text/javascript",
                                "exec": [
                                    "const res = pm.response.json();",
                                    "if (res && res.data && res.data.accessToken) {",
                                    "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.data.accessToken);",
                                    "    console.log('Refreshed accessToken saved');",
                                    "}"
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh-token", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "refresh-token"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** anyone with a valid `refreshToken` cookie (set automatically by Postman's cookie jar after Login runs in the same session).\n\nIssues a new `accessToken` only — the refresh token itself is not rotated."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Logout",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "logout"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** anyone (public). Clears the `accessToken`/`refreshToken` cookies server-side."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get Current User (me)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }],
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "me"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** any authenticated user, any role. Identical to `User > Get My Profile (me)` — kept here too since the assignment spec documents it at this exact path."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "User",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Register",
                    "event": [
                        {
                            "listen": "test",
                            "script": {
                                "type": "text/javascript",
                                "exec": [
                                    "const res = pm.response.json();",
                                    "if (res && res.data && res.data.user) {",
                                    "    const role = res.data.user.role;",
                                    "    if (role === 'CUSTOMER') pm.collectionVariables.set('customerId', res.data.user.id);",
                                    "    if (role === 'TECHNICIAN') pm.collectionVariables.set('technicianId', res.data.user.id);",
                                    "}"
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Jane Customer\",\n  \"email\": \"jane.customer@fixmate.dev\",\n  \"password\": \"Secret123!\",\n  \"phone\": \"+8801700000000\"\n}\n\n// -- TECHNICIAN register (comment out the block above, uncomment this one) --\n// {\n//   \"name\": \"Sam Technician\",\n//   \"email\": \"sam.technician@fixmate.dev\",\n//   \"password\": \"Secret123!\",\n//   \"phone\": \"+8801700000001\",\n//   \"role\": \"TECHNICIAN\"\n// }\n\n// Note: ADMIN is not a selectable role here on purpose -- nobody should be able\n// to self-register as an admin through a public endpoint. Admin accounts are seeded directly."
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/register", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "users", "register"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** anyone (public).\n\nActive body: CUSTOMER (role omitted -> defaults to CUSTOMER). Uncomment the TECHNICIAN block to register a technician instead — it also auto-creates an empty Technician Profile.\n\nDoes **not** auto-login — run `Auth > Login` afterward to get tokens."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get My Profile (me)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }],
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/me", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "users", "me"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** any authenticated user, any role. Returns whichever account's `accessToken` is currently saved in the collection variables."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Update My Profile",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PATCH",
                        "header": [
                            { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
                            { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"bio\": \"I need my sink fixed\",\n  \"address\": \"Dhaka, BD\",\n  \"phone\": \"+8801700000099\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/update-profile", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "users", "update-profile"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** any authenticated user, any role. All fields optional — `name`/`phone` update the User row, `bio`/`profilePhoto`/`address` update the Profile row."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Update My Password",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PATCH",
                        "header": [
                            { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
                            { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"oldPassword\": \"Secret123!\",\n  \"newPassword\": \"NewSecret123!\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/update-password", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "users", "update-password"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** any authenticated user, any role. After running this, `Auth > Login`'s saved password will be stale for this account — log in with `NewSecret123!` afterward, or skip this request during a full run-through."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Categories",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Get All",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/categories?page=1&limit=10",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "categories"],
                            "query": [
                                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                                { "key": "limit", "value": "10" },
                                { "key": "searchTerm", "value": "", "disabled": true }
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** anyone (public)."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Services",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Get All",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/services?page=1&limit=10",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "services"],
                            "query": [
                                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                                { "key": "limit", "value": "10" },
                                { "key": "categoryId", "value": "{{categoryId}}", "disabled": true },
                                { "key": "searchTerm", "value": "", "disabled": true }
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** anyone (public). Filter by `categoryId`, search by `searchTerm` (matches title/description)."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get One",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/services/{{serviceId}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "services", "{{serviceId}}"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** anyone (public)."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Technicians",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Get All",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/technicians?page=1&limit=10",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "technicians"],
                            "query": [
                                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                                { "key": "limit", "value": "10" },
                                { "key": "searchTerm", "value": "", "disabled": true }
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** anyone (public). Only returns users with `role: TECHNICIAN` and `activeStatus: ACTIVE`."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get One (with reviews)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/technicians/{{technicianId}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "technicians", "{{technicianId}}"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** anyone (public). Includes the technician's active services and every review they've received."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Bookings",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Create",
                    "event": [
                        {
                            "listen": "test",
                            "script": {
                                "type": "text/javascript",
                                "exec": [
                                    "const res = pm.response.json();",
                                    "if (res && res.data && res.data.id) {",
                                    "    pm.collectionVariables.set('bookingId', res.data.id);",
                                    "    console.log('Saved bookingId: ' + res.data.id);",
                                    "}"
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
                            { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"serviceId\": \"{{serviceId}}\",\n  \"scheduledAt\": \"2026-08-15T10:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"note\": \"Leaking kitchen sink\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/bookings", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "bookings"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** CUSTOMER only.\n\n`serviceId` must reference an existing, active Service. The technician is derived automatically from the service — you never send `technicianId`. Saves the new booking's id as `bookingId`."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get All (mine)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/bookings?page=1&limit=10",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "bookings"],
                            "query": [
                                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                                { "key": "limit", "value": "10" },
                                { "key": "status", "value": "", "disabled": true }
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** CUSTOMER only. Returns only bookings belonging to the logged-in customer."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get One",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }],
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/bookings/{{bookingId}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "bookings", "{{bookingId}}"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** CUSTOMER only, and only the customer who owns this booking (403 otherwise)."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Cancel",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PATCH",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }],
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/bookings/{{bookingId}}/cancel", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "bookings", "{{bookingId}}", "cancel"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** CUSTOMER only, and only the owner. Only allowed while status is `REQUESTED`, `ACCEPTED`, or `PAID` — fails with 400 once `IN_PROGRESS` or later, matching the spec's cancellation rule."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Payments",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Create (Stripe Checkout)",
                    "event": [
                        {
                            "listen": "test",
                            "script": {
                                "type": "text/javascript",
                                "exec": [
                                    "const res = pm.response.json();",
                                    "if (res && res.data && res.data.payment) {",
                                    "    pm.collectionVariables.set('paymentId', res.data.payment.id);",
                                    "    console.log('Checkout URL: ' + res.data.checkoutUrl);",
                                    "}"
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
                            { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"bookingId\": \"{{bookingId}}\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/payments/create", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "payments", "create"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** CUSTOMER only, and only the owner of the booking. Booking must be status `ACCEPTED` (a Technician must accept it first via `Technician Self-Service > Update Booking Status`).\n\nReturns a real Stripe test-mode `checkoutUrl` — open it in a browser and pay with card `4242 4242 4242 4242` to complete it."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Confirm (Stripe Webhook)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
                            { "key": "stripe-signature", "value": "PASTE_FROM_STRIPE_CLI" }
                        ],
                        "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/payments/confirm", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "payments", "confirm"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** Stripe only. This is a webhook endpoint, not a normal request — it verifies a cryptographic signature over the raw body and will reject any hand-typed body. Included for reference only. To actually trigger it: run `npm run stripe:webhook` (starts the Stripe CLI listener) and complete a real payment via the `checkoutUrl` from `Create`."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get All (mine)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/payments?page=1&limit=10",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "payments"],
                            "query": [
                                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                                { "key": "limit", "value": "10" },
                                { "key": "status", "value": "", "disabled": true }
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** CUSTOMER only. Returns only payments on bookings the logged-in customer owns."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get One",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }],
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "payments", "{{paymentId}}"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** CUSTOMER only, and only the owner of the underlying booking."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Reviews",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Create",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
                            { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"bookingId\": \"{{bookingId}}\",\n  \"rating\": 5,\n  \"comment\": \"Fixed the leak fast, very professional\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/reviews", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "reviews"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** CUSTOMER only, and only the owner of the booking. Booking must be status `COMPLETED`. `rating` must be an integer 1-5. One review per booking (enforced by a unique constraint) — a second attempt returns 409."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Technician Self-Service",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Update My Profile",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PUT",
                        "header": [
                            { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
                            { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"skills\": [\"plumbing\", \"pipe fitting\"],\n  \"experienceYears\": 8,\n  \"isAvailable\": true\n}"
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/technician/profile", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "technician", "profile"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** TECHNICIAN only. All fields optional — send only what changes."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Update My Availability",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PUT",
                        "header": [
                            { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
                            { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"slots\": [\n    { \"dayOfWeek\": 1, \"startTime\": \"09:00\", \"endTime\": \"17:00\" },\n    { \"dayOfWeek\": 3, \"startTime\": \"10:00\", \"endTime\": \"18:00\" }\n  ]\n}"
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/technician/availability", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "technician", "availability"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** TECHNICIAN only. Replaces the ENTIRE weekly schedule every time (not additive) — send the complete set of slots you want. `dayOfWeek`: 0=Sunday...6=Saturday. Times in 24h `HH:mm`."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Get My Bookings",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/technician/bookings?page=1&limit=10",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "technician", "bookings"],
                            "query": [
                                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                                { "key": "limit", "value": "10" },
                                { "key": "status", "value": "", "disabled": true }
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** TECHNICIAN only. Returns only bookings assigned to the logged-in technician."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Update Booking Status",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PATCH",
                        "header": [
                            { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
                            { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"ACCEPTED\"\n}\n\n// This one endpoint drives the whole booking state machine -- swap the\n// \"status\" value depending on where the booking currently is:\n//\n//   current REQUESTED   -> \"ACCEPTED\" or \"DECLINED\"\n//   current PAID         -> \"IN_PROGRESS\"\n//   current IN_PROGRESS  -> \"COMPLETED\"\n//\n// Any other transition (e.g. REQUESTED straight to COMPLETED) is rejected\n// with a 400 that names exactly which transitions ARE legal right now."
                        },
                        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/technician/bookings/{{bookingId}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "technician", "bookings", "{{bookingId}}"] },
                        "description": "**Who can call this:** TECHNICIAN only, and only the technician assigned to this booking (403 otherwise).\n\nSee the body comment for the full legal-transition table. This single endpoint replaces what would otherwise be four separate accept/decline/start/complete routes."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
